<title>BELGIUM: Waigel's gold proposal not out of line - EU source.</title>
<headline>Waigel's gold proposal not out of line - EU source.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-05-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>German Finance Minister Theo Waigel's proposal to revalue Bundesbank gold reserves is in line with practice of most other European central banks and by no means a way of &quot;cooking the books,&quot; an EU monetary official said.</p>
<p>&quot;What the Bundesbank would do (if the proposal is followed) is precisely what other central banks are doing. It is not cooking its books, quite the opposite in fact,&quot; the official, who declined to be identified said.</p>
</text>
